  "meta": {
    "title": "Poetry",
    "subtitle": "The path through the poem",
    "intro": "Poetry is not an ornament of Sufism — it is its freest voice. Where the treatise would freeze, the poem suggests. Where prose explains, the verse enchants. This anthology is built slowly, poem after poem — each given in its original language, its transliteration, its English translation, its context, and a question for meditation."
